## Component Organization Patterns

### File Structure Template

```typescript
// 1. Imports
import React from "react";
import { IconName } from "lucide-react";
import { LocalComponent } from "./LocalComponent";

// 2. Types/Interfaces (if needed)
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  // ...
}

// 3. Sub-components (if tightly coupled)
const SubComponent = ({ data }: { data: string }) => <div>{data}</div>;

// 4. Main component (default or named export)
export const MainComponent: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ title }) => {
  return (
    <section>
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      <SubComponent data="example" />
    </section>
  );
};
```

### Co-located Sub-components

**When to co-locate:**

- ✅ Used only by parent component
- ✅ Tightly coupled to parent's logic
- ✅ Small and focused (< 50 lines)
- ✅ Doesn't need to be reused elsewhere

**Examples in codebase:**

- `DashboardMockup` inside `Hero.tsx` (~160 lines)
- `MiniInbox`, `MiniPipeline`, `MiniCalendar` inside `BenefitsSection.tsx`
- `FeatureCard` inside `FeaturesSection.tsx`
- `RoleCard`, `AvatarCluster` inside `RoleSection.tsx`
- `ToggleItem` inside `PricingSection.tsx`
- `LogoPlaceholder` inside `TrustedLogos.tsx`

**When to extract:**

- ❌ Reused in multiple components
- ❌ Complex logic (> 50 lines)
- ❌ Needs its own tests
- ❌ Part of design system

