/contexts/       - React Context providers (no global state)
/lib/            - Third-party integrations (none yet)
/pages/          - Page components (single-page app)
/layouts/        - Layout wrappers (App.tsx handles it)
/styles/         - CSS files (all Tailwind utilities)
/tests/          - Test files (no tests yet)
/assets/         - Images, fonts (using CDNs)
/api/            - API routes (no backend)
/config/         - Runtime config (vite.config.ts at root)
```

**When to add these:**

- Create `/hooks/` when you have 2+ custom hooks
- Create `/utils/` when you have reusable helper functions
- Create `/types/` when types are shared across 3+ files
- Create `/services/` when adding API integration
- Create `/contexts/` when adding global state (Zustand/Context API)

