## Anti-patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Don't Mix Concerns

```typescript
// ❌ Bad - mixing UI with data fetching
export const UserList = () => {
  const [users, setUsers] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/api/users").then(/* ... */);
  }, []);

  return <div>{/* render */}</div>;
};

// ✅ Good - separate concerns when you add backend
// services/userService.ts
export const fetchUsers = () => {
  /* ... */
};

// components/UserList.tsx
export const UserList = () => {
  const { data } = useQuery("users", fetchUsers);
  return <div>{/* render */}</div>;
};
```

### ❌ Don't Create Unnecessary Nesting

```typescript
// ❌ Bad - unnecessary folder depth
/components/ceinosst /
  hero /
  Hero.tsx /
  // ✅ Good - flat when possible
  components /
  Hero.tsx;
```

### ❌ Don't Default Export Everything

```typescript
// ❌ Bad - hard to refactor
export default function Button() {}

// ✅ Good - named exports for components
export const Button: React.FC = () => {};
```

